<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Hull Papers</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-30">August 30,
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the President</hi>
                            </p>
                            <p>In accordance with our conversation today, I am sending you herewith
                                a draft of a declaration by the United Nations on dependent
                                    peoples<note n="1" xml:id="d644fn1">No draft is attached to the
                                    source text in the Hull papers, and the original of this
                                    memorandum has not been found in the Roosevelt Papers. The
                                    attachment was probably the text of March 9, 1943, printed <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_717">p.
                                    717</ref>.</note> for use in connection with your conversations
                                with Prime Minister Churchill.</p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>